sentences: Christopher Todd Feinstein (May 26, 1967 – December 15, 2009) was an American bass guitarist, record producer, and songwriter from Nashville, Tennessee.
In 1997, Feinstein moved to New York City to pursue his career in production.

Together, Feinstein and Tudor co-produced material for the Beatles-based soundtrack to the 2001 drama film I Am Sam, featuring Rufus Wainright and Sean Lennon's "Across the Universe" and Howie Day's "Help!".

In 2006, Feinstein was sought-after to play bass guitar for Ryan Adams & The Cardinals.
